ers junior hockey club from its establishment in  until  contents  early life  hockey ventures  personal life  references  external links early lifeedit the oldest of three sons of a greek immigrant family who owned a small restaurant in detroit karmanos attended henry ford high school and graduated from wayne state university in  soon after leaving college he founded software company compuware with two partners thomas thewes and allen cutting karmanos served as compuwares ceo until june   when he became executive chairman karmanos retired from compuware on march   but maintained a consultant role within the company compuware terminated his postretirement consulting agreement effective october   he has since opened a new computer firm mad dog technology hockey venturesedit karmanos cofounded the detroit compuware hockey organization in the late s with thewes the organization includes all levels of hockey from recreational to aaa and junior a the ontario hockey league awarded an expansion franchise on december   to be known as the detroit compuware ambassadors the team later became the detroit junior red wings detroit whalers and then plymouth whalers following a relocation to nearby plymouth in  karmanos sold the whalers to the owners of flints perani arena and event center and the franchise was renamed flint firebirds he also sold the plymouth arena to usa hockey karmanos his compuware partner thewes and former player jim rutherford purchased the hartford whalers in  for  million at the time they had committed to keeping the team in hartford for at least four years connecticuts thengovernor lowell p weicker announced that karmanos would be critical for the team to stay in hartford weicker later became a member of the compuware board of directors karmanos was unable to sell  season tickets in hartford during the – nhl season and announced the team would leave hartford before a new city had been found if the whalers were unable to sell  season tickets for the – season even though they surpassed  season tickets in  the team was moved to raleigh north carolina and renamed the carolina hurricanes following the – season as a result karmanos is still reviled by many people in connecticut the hurricanes went on to win the stanley cup in  with karmanos eagerly donning his skates hoisting the cup and skating around with it briefly after the game win for his day with the cup he brought it to compuware hq in detroit and allowed employees to get their photo taken individually with the cup karmanos gale force holdings has a subsidiary dedicated to the nhl hurricanes holdings llc which includes the hurricanes and their stadium pnc arena the holdings also include the hurricaness echl affiliate florida everblades along with stadium germain arena in fort myers florida karmanos received the lester patrick trophy for outstanding service to hockey after the – season the bill long award in  for services to the ontario hockey league and was inducted to the united states hockey hall of fame in  he was inducted to the hockey hall of fame in the builder category in  karmanos also sponsors youth hockey programs in michigan under his backing karmanos youth hockey teams have accumulated numerous state national and international tournaments personal lifeedit karmanos donated money to the michigan cancer foundation which was renamed the barbara ann karmanos cancer institute in  in memory of his first wife barbara ann karmanos who died of breast cancer in  in addition to three children with barbara karmanos has four others with current wife danialle and nine grandchildren referencesedit    adams alan   people of power and influence the hockey news    accessdate requires url help  httpwwwcrainsdetroitcomarticleblogthingsyoumaynotknowaboutpetekarmanosjrwhoretiresfrom  a b c hurricanes karmanos a true hockey builder nhlcom  karmanos stepping down as compuware corps ceo june     a golden parachute will gently carry pete karmanos into retirement march     depart